# 🔧 Hardware Design Documentation  

---

## 📌 Overview  

This directory contains all hardware-related resources for the Modular MCU Platform, including PCB designs, schematics, and component details.

---

## 🧩 Design Highlights  

- Multi-layer PCB design  
- Modular socket interface for MCU interchangeability  
- Optimized routing for signal integrity  
- Scalable hardware architecture  

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used  

- KiCad / Altium Designer  
- Standard PCB fabrication workflows  

---

## 📁 Contents  

- Schematics  
- PCB layout files  
- Bill of Materials (BOM)  
- Gerber files (for fabrication)  

---

## ⚡ Design Considerations  

- Power distribution efficiency  
- Signal integrity across connectors  
- Mechanical durability of module interface  
- Thermal management  

---

## 🧠 Notes  

The hardware is designed to support multiple microcontrollers with different pin configurations through a unified interface, enabling rapid prototyping and system scalability.
